 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/ukensie.showPublicProfile?language=EN>kensie</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#330000>(12/16/00 8:53 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmfrm17.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=261.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Pets and Weapoons</span><hr size=1> enchanter pets don't dual-wield until later. Don't remember the exact level, somewhere around 30 I think. The pet changes were to allow mage and necro pets to attack with both hands regardless of whether they held weapons or not. From what I understand, it had no effect on enchanter pets. <p>Kensie Graeme<BR>
Lvl 37 Enchanter<BR>
Bukaru (lvl 16 rogue)<BR>
Silarix (lvl 9 iksar shammy)<BR>
Officer, Veeshan Guard</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#deddbf><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/uartiethebold.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Artie the Bold</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://brotherhood.rpg-guilds.com/artie/comets.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#330000>(12/18/00 12:11 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmfrm17.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=261.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://brotherhood.rpg-guilds.com/artie/Artie.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Pets and Weapoons</span><hr size=1> No wonder I haven't seen Botox on in a while. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
The only time pets gain an advantage from a weapon is if its base damage is higher than the pet's natural damage. This is only possible at low levels, or if you've got some uber-weapon.<br>
<br>
For now you may see benefit from giving your pet a rusty two-handed scythe or equivalent, but in a few spell levels the damage will be less than your pet's natural damage anyway.<br>
<br>
Once you hit your mid- to late-teens, though, you'll probably find yourself using your pet less often, especially in grouping situations. Until then, though, they are nice for extra damage.<br>
<br>
At level 29, your pets have a chance at least to dual-wield if given a one-handed weapon. Give him a speed buff, and he's hell on wheels against green mobs you're trying to clear out, or that giant you're fear-kiting. Just don't let him take more than a couple of hits. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Oh, and to confirm Kensie's statement ... enchanter pets do not get the ability to automatically dual-wield upon summoning post-34. This recent enhancement was only for mage, necro, and shadowknight pets. *boggle* <p><body bgcolor="#FFFFFF">

